Demand Response as a "Solar Cloud" Filter: If your 15-minute average solar export starts to drop, instead of immediately reverting to the Schedule, you could trigger a SetDemandResponse(true, 2.0). This tells the AC: "Stay on, but relax the target by 2 degrees to save power until the clouds pass."

The Humidity Override: You noticed your humidity dot was high in your Grafana dump. If IndoorHumidity > 60%, you could trigger SetDehumidifySetpoint(ctx, 45). This often forces the Daikin into a "Dry" cycle logic where it prioritizes moisture removal over raw temperature drop—perfect for wet weekends.
